passes.benefit_text:
This pass is an e-voucher. Admits up to 4 at $5-off each (Not to be combined with other discounts; not valid for member pricing). Expires 11/30/26
For general information about the museum, please call 978-369-9763 or visit https://concordmuseum.org/. &nbsp;
The museum is open Tuesday - Sunday as well as some Monday holidays. Please confirm museum hours via phone or website before planning your visit.&nbsp;

The library’s pass admits up to 4 people into the museum&nbsp; free of charge. Special event admission is not included under the library pass discount.&nbsp;
Free parking is available behind the museum with direct elevator access to our galleries.
Regular admission prices: Adults, $7; Seniors (65+) and Framingham residents with ID, $6; Students (High school + college (with ID), $5.00; Children under 13, free.&nbsp;

This pass admits 3 visitors to Discovery Woods and the Discovery Museum at 1/2 price admission ($9.50) per person ; any additional visitors must pay the regular admission price of $19.00
Reservations are no longer needed or accepted. Please present this pass to Admissions staff when checking in and the discount will be applied to the cost of your visit.&nbsp;&nbsp;
This pass is an e-voucher - discount code will be included in reservation confirmation email which will be received upon reserving the pass. Please contact the reference desk at 781-259-8465 x204 with any questions about the pass.

Two passes per day. Each pass admits one person. 50% discount on admission, $1 fee for children.
Timed tickets are not necessary, but if purchasing in advance is preferred tickets can be purchased online at https://www.nativeplanttrust.org/visit/garden-woods/
If purchasing tickets in advance, choose the Library Pass option and bring the library pass with you to Garden in the Woods.&nbsp;
No discounts on classes, tours, or retail items.&nbsp;
Please note that schedule is subject to change and that hours will be reduced after October 18. Please be sure to check the&nbsp; website for exact dates and hours before planning your visit.&nbsp;

This pass discount provides $10 admission for up to 2 individuals. Advanced ticket reservations made in advance of visit are strongly encouraged on the museum's website. Directions and information regarding the digital pass use will be provided in your confirmation email.&nbsp;
A reminder that the address of the ICA is 25 Harbor Shore Drive, Boston, MA 02210.
More information on library membership, exhibitions, and programs can be found on our website at www.icaboston.org . For ticketing or general inquiries, please contact our Visitor Services team at visitorservices@icaboston.org. or by calling 617-478-3100.&nbsp;
Children under 17 are always free. Free Thursday nights 5:00 - 9:00 pm. Tickets for free Thursday nights are available online starting at 10 am on the day of the event.
Library Passes are not valid for performances, events, or films.&nbsp;

Each pass provides up to four (4) people with a $5 discount per person—children under the age of 18 are always admitted free. Timed ticket reservations must be made in advance of visit with library e-voucher on the museum's website. Directions and information regarding e-voucher use will be provided in your confirmation email.&nbsp;
For more information about the museum, please visit https://www.gardnermuseum.org/visit.
MUSEUM HOURS:&nbsp;
WEEKDAYS 11 AM – 5 PM | WEEKENDS 10 AM – 5 PM | THURSDAYS 11 AM – 9 PM | CLOSED TUESDAYS
Please note that reserving a library pass does not guarantee that space will be available on your preferred date.&nbsp;

This one-day Library Partner Admission Pass admits up to 4 people to a Mass Audubon wildlife sanctuary including (but not limited to) Drumlin Farm. With this pass, admission is discounted to $2 per visitor over the age of 2.
This pass is an e-voucher - there is nothing to pick up at the library.&nbsp;
Please visit https://www.massaudubon.org/get-outdoors/wildlife-sanctuaries/trails for the latest information, including safety guidelines.
Open hours and dates vary by sanctuary and some sites are open during some Monday holidays, so please contact Mass Audubon to confirm they are open before reserving the pass with the Library.&nbsp;
Please note that Drumlin Farm is currently open Tuesday–Sunday, as well as many Monday holidays.&nbsp; Please check the website of the attraction you are interested in to confirm hours/schedule before planning your visit.&nbsp;

Each pass admits 1 vehicle for free.&nbsp;&nbsp; Please note that reserving a library pass does not guarantee that space will be available on your preferred date.&nbsp; Passes may be checked out for 1 day and are due back before library opens the day following use.&nbsp;
This is a physical pass that must be picked up at the Reference Desk. Please call 781-259-8465 x 3 with any questions.&nbsp;
Please note that the Main Beach at Walden pond will be closed for the 2025 summer season due to construction.&nbsp;

Each pass allows admission for 2 adults at $15 each (general admission and special exhibition) and up to 4 children ages 7–17 at $10 each (special exhibition only). There is no discount for children 7–17 for general admission, currently $10.&nbsp; K-12 educators are always admitted for free with school ID. Children 6 and under are admitted free.&nbsp;
Pass provides discount code to be used for booking tickets online. Discount code provided in reservation email, or you can reach a librarian at 781-259-8465 (press 3)&nbsp; lincoln@minlib.net to receive code by phone.
Timed tickets must be booked online at https://www.mfa.org/tickets.&nbsp; ***When you reach the page for the date you have already chosen and "General Admission" at the top, you will find a PROMO CODE box at the top on the right.&nbsp; Type in the Promo Code, and Submit, to see the Library Pass options appear.
Proof of COVID-19 vaccination to enter the Museum is no longer required in accordance with the City of Boston’s mandate. Please visit the page&nbsp; here for more information.&nbsp;
Please note that reserving a library pass does not guarantee that space will be available on your preferred date. &nbsp;
